properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 11 at 9:32PM CST until February 13 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Accumulating snow Wednesday afternoon through Wednesday
night...

.Snow, possibly mixed with rain to start, will overspread parts
of far northeast Missouri, far southeast Iowa, and west central
Illinois after noon on Wednesday and continuing through Wednesday
night. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches are expected.
Significantly colder air will move into the area Thursday with
some blowing snow possible.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...Portions of northeast Missouri, southeast Iowa and
west central Illinois.

* WHEN...From noon Wednesday to 6 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions.
In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.
In Missouri, call 800-222-6400 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON WEDNESDAY TO 6 AM CST THURSDAY
